{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.40",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 40,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 40",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 40 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:1",
      "text": "Moreover the Lord answered Job, and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:2",
      "text": "Shall he that contendeth with the Almighty instruct him? he that reproveth God, let him answer it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:3",
      "text": "Then Job answered the Lord, and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:4",
      "text": "Behold, I am vile; what shall I answer thee? I will lay mine hand upon my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:5",
      "text": "Once have I spoken; but I will not answer: yea, twice; but I will proceed no further.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:6",
      "text": "Then answered the Lord unto Job out of the whirlwind, and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:7",
      "text": "Gird up thy loins now like a man: I will demand of thee, and declare thou unto me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:8",
      "text": "Wilt thou also disannul my judgment? wilt thou condemn me, that thou mayest be righteous?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:9",
      "text": "Hast thou an arm like God? or canst thou thunder with a voice like him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:10",
      "text": "Deck thyself now with majesty and excellency; and array thyself with glory and beauty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:11",
      "text": "Cast abroad the rage of thy wrath: and behold every one that is proud, and abase him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:12",
      "text": "Look on every one that is proud, and bring him low; and tread down the wicked in their place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:13",
      "text": "Hide them in the dust together; and bind their faces in secret.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:14",
      "text": "Then will I also confess unto thee that thine own right hand can save thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:15",
      "text": "Behold now behemoth, which I made with thee; he eateth grass as an ox.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:16",
      "text": "Lo now, his strength is in his loins, and his force is in the navel of his belly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:17",
      "text": "He moveth his tail like a cedar: the sinews of his stones are wrapped together.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:18",
      "text": "His bones are as strong pieces of brass; his bones are like bars of iron.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:19",
      "text": "He is the chief of the ways of God: he that made him can make his sword to approach unto him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:20",
      "text": "Surely the mountains bring him forth food, where all the beasts of the field play.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:21",
      "text": "He lieth under the shady trees, in the covert of the reed, and fens.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:22",
      "text": "The shady trees cover him with their shadow; the willows of the brook compass him about.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:23",
      "text": "Behold, he drinketh up a river, and hasteth not: he trusteth that he can draw up Jordan into his mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.40.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:24",
      "text": "He taketh it with his eyes: his nose pierceth through snares.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
